---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="I'm Zori, a freelance developer and creator of Notion templates for freelancers who want to get better organized."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="page-header__title">About</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow prose">
      <p>
        Hi, I'm Zori. PHP/Laravel developer by trade, freelancer by experience.
        Like any freelancer, there came a point when managing clients, projects and invoices
        in Excel or scattered notes became unsustainable.
      </p>
      <p>
        I discovered Notion and started building my own systems. Over time, those systems became
        so useful that I decided to share them — and sell them.
      </p>
      <p>
        The templates you'll find here are not the typical designer-made ones that look pretty
        but have zero logic behind them. They're built by a developer, with relational databases,
        advanced formulas, and with a real understanding of how a technical freelancer's day-to-day actually works.
      </p>
      <h2>This blog</h2>
      <p>
        Here I publish practical guides on how to get better organized as a freelancer: client management,
        project tracking, invoicing, and how to make the most of Notion without spending hours on configuration.
      </p>
      <a href="/en/templates/" class="btn btn--primary">See the templates</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header { padding: 3.5rem 0 2.5rem; background: var(--color-surface); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .page-header__title { font-size: 2.25rem; font-weight: 800; }
  .section { padding: 3rem 0 5rem; }
</style>
